			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">PVC Waste Gas</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">聚氯乙烯废气</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">PVC Pyrolysis Gas; PVC Decomposition Gas</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">PVC Pyrolysis Gas; PVC Decomposition Gas</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Wastes</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Production residues</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">PVC waste gas is a byproduct of the PVC manufacturing process. It is produced when PVC is heated to extremely high temperatures, between 300⁰C and 900⁰C, in a process called pyrolysis. This process breaks down the plastic into smaller molecules, transforming it into pyrolysis oil or gas. This product can then be used as a fuel or to create new, second-life plastic products. The plastic also breaks down to glycolic acid, which is used in the cosmetics industry, and the CO2 is converted into syngas, a simple fuel.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">PVC 废气是 PVC 生产过程中产生的副产品。当 PVC 被加热到极高温度（300⁰C 到 900⁰C）时就会产生这种气体，这个过程被称为热解。这一过程将塑料分解成更小的分子，转化成热解油或气体。这种产品随后可用作燃料或制造新的、可二次使用的塑料产品。塑料还可分解为乙醇酸，用于化妆品行业，二氧化碳则可转化为合成气，一种简单的燃料。</common:generalComment>
